  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The article \"OER by Discipline Guide: Reducing Barriers and Building Sustainability for OER Adoption,\" authored by Sarah Adams and Savannah Sillito, aims to enhance the adoption of Open Educational Resources (OER) within higher education. It aligns with the Sustainable Development Goal of Quality Education, focusing on creating sustainable and inclusive educational practices through OER.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This 2023 publication in Open MIND serves as a foundational guide for institutions seeking to mitigate barriers to OER adoption. The authors highlight the increasing relevance of OER in fostering accessibility and affordability in education while emphasizing the importance of sustainability in educational practices. By targeting disciplines where OER can be most impactful, the guide aspires to deliver actionable insights for educational institutions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although the article has yet to receive formal citations and mentions since its release, its focus on sustainability and educational policy underscores its potential for influencing institutional strategies towards more inclusive learning environments. As higher education continues to evolve in response to economic and technological changes, resources that advocate for open education will likely become vital components in institutional planning.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The guide not only addresses current trends in the landscape of higher education but also embodies a commitment to advancing quality education\u2014an objective echoed in the United Nations\u2019 Sustainable Development Goals. By reinforcing the need for equitable access to educational resources, this work is poised to shape future discussions surrounding academic integrity and resource distribution.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, while the data surrounding the article\u2019s immediate impact is limited, its foundational insights about OER and sustainability present a critical framework for educators and policymakers. As awareness around OER continues to grow, the strategies articulated in this guide may well serve as a benchmark for future studies in the realm of open education.</p>",
